Kolade Adeyemi, KanoGovernor Abdullahi Umar Ganduje has announced the complete lockdown of the state, for one week with effect from Thursday , 16, April, 2020. Ganduje made this announcement during a meeting with religious leaders this evening at the Government House. According to him,this is a complete lockdown of the state, where there is no market, no social activities, no mosque, no Church and people should stay at home. He urged residents to cooperate and support this decision, as a measure to prevent the spread of this dreaded COVID-19 in the state. Details shortly…. The Nation Muslim faithful in some parts of the country yesterday ignored the directive by the various state governments on social distancing in order to curtail the spread of COVID- 19 as they thronged the mosques enmass to observe the juma’at prayers. This happened in Kano, Yola and Ughelli in Delta state.… April 4, 2020 In "News" As part of measures to stop the spread of Coronavirus, Abdullahi Ganduje, governor of Kano state has declared a one-day fasting and prayer in the state. Ganduje told residents to observe the fast and pray on Monday. The governor said this while speaking on Sunday during the inauguration of the… March 30, 2020 In "News" Governor Abdullahi Umar Ganduje of Kano state and his wife Prof. Hafsat Abdullahi Ganduje have received their coronavirus test results. The results showed that the two tested negative for COVID-19. “We thank Almighty Allah for this result which shows negative. That is how He (Allah) wishes. All those whose results… April 2, 2020 In "Politics"